cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper presents an automatic robot-based charging station with 3D vision guidance for plugging and unplugging the charger. The main focus of the paper is on the robot motion planning procedure for plug-in, which falls under the domain of robotics. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper extensively uses 3D vision system and shape-based matching methods to identify and get the exact pose of the charging port. This falls under the domain of computer vision and pattern recognition. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses machine learning algorithms for shape-based matching and calibration of the camera-robot system. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper presents a system consisting of a 3D vision system, an UR10 robot and a charging station. The system is designed to automatically charge electric and plug-in hybrid vehicles, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper presents a series of successful experiments demonstrating the functionality of the robot-based charging station. The experiments involve multimedia elements such as videos and images. This falls under the domain of multimedia.
